snippet: The court referred the election law to the Supreme Constitutional Court, adding to the uncertainty about a vote that had been scheduled to begin as early as April 22.
abstract: Top Egyptian court cancels pending parliamentary elections and refers election law to Supreme Constitutional Court; decision adds to mounting uncertainty about vote and once again plunges Egypt's political transition back into legal limbo.
lead_paragraph: The court referred the election law to the Supreme Constitutional Court, adding to the uncertainty about a vote that had been scheduled to begin as early as April 22.
